extends layout

block content
  div.narrow
    h1= title
    p.new We now support WebSockets! Come play with 
      a(href='websocket.html') the demo
      | .
    p Capture the raw HTTP requests sent to a URL, so you can debug the stuff you get from webhooks. Based on the 
      a(href='http://requestb.in', target='_blank') PostBin
      |  written in python. Made with 
      a(href='http://nodejs.org', target='_blank') node.js
      |  and 
      a(href='http://expressjs.com', target='_blank') express.js
      | . It's an more visually pleasing alternative to 
      code nc -l 
      | or 
      code tcpdump -x
      | .
    p Each bin stores a maximum of 10 requests. Bins are removed if they have not been accessed for at least 48 hours.
    p The source for this project is freely 
      a(href='https://github.com/badassdon/postbin-node', target='_blank') available on github
      |  under the MIT License.

    a.button(href='/inspect/'+newId) Create Bin

    if recentBins.length
      p
        h3 Recent Bins
        ul
          each recent in recentBins
            li
              a(href='/inspect/#{recent}') /#{recent}

    footer Created by 
      a(href='http://www.badassdon.com', target='_blank') badassdon
      | .
 
